subject: Add objectstorage flavor and extra blockdevices option
revisions:
[{'number': 3, 'created': '2016-08-26 15:19:28.000000000', 'files': ['doc/source/configuration.rst', 'roles/common/defaults/main.yml', 'roles/libvirt/setup/overcloud/tasks/main.yml'], 'message': 'Add objectstorage flavor and extra blockdevices option

This patch adds an option to create three additional blockdevices per
node. The devices are created as sparse files, therefore not using space
before being used. The option can be used in any flavor, and a new
flavor for Swift has been added that makes use of it.  It is especially
useful to test Swift and other storage setups; and by using three
blockdevices per node one can even test a triple-replicated setup with a
single object storage node.

Change-Id: I3960065916b93bb7616d509e7b72c579f7362efe
'}]
commit_message:
Add objectstorage flavor and extra blockdevices option

This patch adds an option to create three additional blockdevices per
node. The devices are created as sparse files, therefore not using space
before being used. The option can be used in any flavor, and a new
flavor for Swift has been added that makes use of it.  It is especially
useful to test Swift and other storage setups; and by using three
blockdevices per node one can even test a triple-replicated setup with a
single object storage node.

Change-Id: I3960065916b93bb7616d509e7b72c579f7362efe

"add_<resource>_to_<other_resource>" and
"remove_<resource>_from_<other_resource>" naming convention, namely with

commit_message:
Adjust router add/remove interface method names

We previously had add_ip_to_port and remove_ip_from_port in 2014 and
recently with refactorings have gone the way of having
"add_<resource>_to_<other_resource>" and
"remove_<resource>_from_<other_resource>" naming convention, namely with
the compute refactoring (and one other I'm forgetting).

We should make sure names stay in line with that format and get these
changed up.

Change-Id: Ie123971565bd7e4c2fb76c9d54f85eddcd983757

subject: Preserve the shell environment for run-validation
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2016-09-06 09:20:15.000000000', 'files': ['scripts/run-validation'], 'message': 'Preserve the shell environment for run-validation

The undercloud validations are being run as root via `sudo` called by
Ansible. This strips the shell environment variables (most notably the
undercloud OpenStack credentials) and the validations have no way of
getting these reliably if they need them.

This configures Ansible to pass `-E` to `sudo`, which will preserve the
environment.

Change-Id: Ie88c4167f57c75bc99dcfa5ff504028e8c47721a
'}]
commit_message:
Preserve the shell environment for run-validation

The undercloud validations are being run as root via `sudo` called by
Ansible. This strips the shell environment variables (most notably the
undercloud OpenStack credentials) and the validations have no way of
getting these reliably if they need them.

This configures Ansible to pass `-E` to `sudo`, which will preserve the
environment.

Change-Id: Ie88c4167f57c75bc99dcfa5ff504028e8c47721a

commit_message:
Disable slave git servers while syncing

Now that the git repository is served from a different process
it is possible for there to be a race condition where the slaves
do not yet have the updated copy of the data before they get a
request for it.

This patch ensures that the git service is shut down on the slave
nodes during the synchronisation of repo data.

Change-Id: I83650253924354d0e63621474ba69f8cf254bde8

commit_message:
Align create role validate procedure

Now, in Nailgun, there is a 'weak' create role
validation procedure that only validates JSON schema.
Meanwhile, 'volumes_roles_mapping' ids are not validated,
that allows create roles with wrong 'volumes_roles_mapping'
metadata. This patch:
  * fixes validate procedure of 'volumes_roles_mapping' ids
    while creating a new role
  * moves validate code for already existed roles from handler
    to validator

Change-Id: Ib040b9bde0f2a54323a36c8e3c2d01716282cbdc
Closes-Bug: 1619486

commit_message:
Separate remote log stream from local

This fix separates the remote log streams from the local
by binding the remote ruleset to the UDP and TCP input modules.
Additionally new overrides are provided to allow for better customization:
``rsyslog_server_logrotation_window`` defaults to 14 days
``rsyslog_server_ratelimit_interval`` defaults to 0 seconds
``rsyslog_server_ratelimit_burst`` defaults to 10000

The rsyslog.conf is also now using v7+ style configuration settings

Change-Id: I5759ea8fb7eaad79d857a335a4aede558aa0067d
Closes-Bug: #1621559

commit_message:
Amend comments regarding configuration of $log_file

This commit updates comments regarding the value of $log_file.  In order
for logging to be sent to stderr, this parameter needs to be unset in
Glance's relevant configuration files and the value of $use_stderr needs
to be set to true.

Setting it to a boolean false results in a logfile called 'False' being
generated, as it's stringified by ::oslo and treated as such by
glance-api and glance-registry.

Change-Id: Ia01e9e7fc665b828a075b2df4c6186e99b5d114d
Closes-Bug: #1621774

commit_message:
Compress test execution logs

The volume of logs we collect in CI jobs are extensive. This
patch ensures that the logs collected are compressed to reduce
the space taken in CI systems.

PYTHONUNBUFFERED is also set to ensure that the console log
from the CI jobs is recorded in the exact order of execution.

Change-Id: Idf85508e52056230bdadba8bccda936f192fb37e
Related-Bug: #1620849

subject: Fix consuming from unbound reply queue
revisions:
[{'number': 2, 'created': '2016-08-05 08:02:38.000000000', 'files': ['oslo_messaging/_drivers/impl_rabbit.py'], 'message': 'Fix consuming from unbound reply queue

Consumer declaration consist of the next steps:
  1) declare an exchange
  2) declare a queue
  3) bind the queue to the exchange

Due to reply exchanges are auto-delete, at the
step 3 the exchange can be removed and consumer.declare()
will raise `queue.bind 404 Exchange not found`.

So, in this case the queue is exist and AMQPListener
just call consumer.consume() on the queue and go to
drain_events() despite on the fact that the queue is
unbound.

Change-Id: Idf5e26a37d7a87e7bf4f340b92f3caffccca318e
Closes-Bug: #1609766
'}]
commit_message:
Fix consuming from unbound reply queue

Consumer declaration consist of the next steps:
  1) declare an exchange
  2) declare a queue
  3) bind the queue to the exchange

Due to reply exchanges are auto-delete, at the
step 3 the exchange can be removed and consumer.declare()
will raise `queue.bind 404 Exchange not found`.

So, in this case the queue is exist and AMQPListener
just call consumer.consume() on the queue and go to
drain_events() despite on the fact that the queue is
unbound.

Change-Id: Idf5e26a37d7a87e7bf4f340b92f3caffccca318e
Closes-Bug: #1609766

commit_message:
Add tests for garbage collection process

After murano Objects and ObjectsCopy started merged during deployment,
destruction dependencies enabled in .init method stop working. The cause
is that now it's impossible to fetch "old" subscriber object to use
during garbage collection.
This problem is solved. Murano will persist destruction dependency in
target object model, and check if it exist or modified.

Also, murano have an error in sorting of must-be-destroyed objects.
Target was deleted after subscriber, and sorting failed in case of
cyclic dependencies. This is solved too.

Test for this cases are introduced in this commit.

Change-Id: I4e8824b6c0e615527d59c6961e3f62065d5c1329
Targets-blueprint: dependency-driven-resource-deallocation
Closes-Bug: #1619248
Closes-Bug: #1619635
